{
  "stem": "25639.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anushka and I were-- she especially-- was very scared for mother's life, because by this time we-- we saw the sort of things that the SS were capable of doing, how quickly a human life ended, just brutally, under the whip of the SS.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "This-- I don't think I could bear seeing that, and my mother being-- become the victim.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "No diamond is worth that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it's really incredible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It's not that she just-- it has nothing to do with wanting to become wealthy, or-- but it had-- she already thought about the time when we will be free.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she wanted to be able to provide for us, as if she expected that we may have nothing left at home, if we ever get out of this hell hole.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was that incident.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We passed it, of course, with flying colors.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We worked in this Kanada work detail 'til October.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And October, I think, the 15th, when the-- something happened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a kommando of women who worked outside of the perimeter of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is Auschwitz to Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And every day, they went out, they worked with-- with gunpowder.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And every day they were searched for gunpowder, because it could be obviously detrimental to the SS to-- to have-- to-- to-- for us to have gunpowder.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what I didn't know at that time, that there was an underground.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I suppose I was too young to be asked to be in the underground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But there was an active underground in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And every day, the women who worked in this gunpowder-- with gunpowder in the factory-- they smuggled out-- out pinches of gunpowder in very special crevices in their bodies.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
